      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n\nfolder 55 - 171\nD-120 concepts as \"bridegroom\" + \"second Advent\" although still intelligible signify something quite other than, say, were he an actual historic person or man-God or son of God. Let us assume Jesus Christ is paradigmatic, + his life is a formula: including + especially the resurrection Yet still there is a \"bridegroom\" + there is a \"second advert\" - i.e. eschatology. What, then, is referred to? Not a certain elevated mental or spiritu",
